Sentencas: The perovskite-related intergrowth oxides, Sr3-xLaxFe2-yCoyO7-delta (0.3 <= x <= 0.6 and 0 <= y <= 0.6), have been investigated as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Sr3-xLaxFe2-yCoyO7-δ (0.3≤x≤0.6 and 0≤y≤0.6) intergrowth oxide cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: With a given La content x, the electrical conductivity, oxide-ion vacancy concentration, and thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) increase with increasing Co content y. With a given Co content, while the electrical conductivity increases, the TEC decreases with increasing La content.
Titulo: Sr3-xLaxFe2-yCoyO7-δ (0.3≤x≤0.6 and 0≤y≤0.6) intergrowth oxide cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrocatalytic activity and power density measured with Sr3-xLaxFe2-yCoyO7-delta/La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O2.8/Ni-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (GDC) single cells with a GDC interlayer between the cathode and electrolyte increase with increasing Co and La contents due to an increase in electrical conductivity and oxide ion vacancy concentration.
Titulo: Sr3-xLaxFe2-yCoyO7-δ (0.3≤x≤0.6 and 0≤y≤0.6) intergrowth oxide cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity, TEC, and electrochemical performance of the Sr3-xLaxFe2-yCoyO7-delta cathodes are also compared with those of the LaSr3Fe3-yCoyO10-delta intergrowth and La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta perovskite oxides.
Titulo: Sr3-xLaxFe2-yCoyO7-δ (0.3≤x≤0.6 and 0≤y≤0.6) intergrowth oxide cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
